<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="500" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1039,1605]" pageId="5" pageNumber="500">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1220,1245]" pageId="5" pageNumber="500">Remarks.</emphasis>
Currently, the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rao in Rao &amp; Clausen" authorityYear="1970" box="[552,681,1220,1245]" class="Gastrotricha (awaiting allocation)" family="Planodasyidae" genus="Planodasys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macrodasyida" pageId="5" pageNumber="500" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[552,681,1220,1245]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="500">Planodasys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes two species both of which are from 
<collectingCountry box="[1184,1242,1220,1245]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="500">India</collectingCountry>
(see also below). Description of both species are based on bright-field microscopy only; it is possible that advanced optical techniques (e.g., DIC) may reveal internal structures so far undetected (e.g., the frontal organ) and/or may provide a better insight on the structure of the very long cylindrical caudal organ (bursa copulatrix in the original description). As the layout of the reproductive system has been demonstrated to be of phylogenetic significance (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Todaro, M. A. &amp; Kanneby, T. &amp; Dal Zotto, M. &amp; Jondelius, U." box="[215,425,1399,1424]" pageId="5" pageNumber="500" pagination="17892" refId="ref10960" refString="Todaro, M. A., Kanneby, T., Dal Zotto, M. &amp; Jondelius, U. (2011) Phylogeny of Thaumastodermatidae (Gastrotricha: Macrodasyida) inferred from nuclear and mitochondrial sequence data. PLoS ONE, 6, e 17892. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0017892" type="journal article" year="2011">
Todaro 
<emphasis box="[302,359,1399,1424]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="500">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
), reliable information in this regard is relevant beyond taxonomy. Likewise, the inclusion of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rao in Rao &amp; Clausen" authorityYear="1970" box="[183,312,1436,1461]" class="Gastrotricha (awaiting allocation)" family="Planodasyidae" genus="Planodasys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macrodasyida" pageId="5" pageNumber="500" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[183,312,1436,1461]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="500">Planodasys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in the ongoing phylogenetic studies based on molecular markers (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Todaro, M. A. &amp; Guidi, L. &amp; Ferraguti, M. &amp; Balsamo, M." box="[1219,1432,1436,1461]" pageId="5" pageNumber="500" pagination="115 - 125" refId="ref10831" refString="Todaro, M. A., Guidi, L., Ferraguti, M. &amp; Balsamo, M. (2012) A fresh look at Dinodasys mirabilis (Gastrotricha, Macrodasyida), with focus on the reproductive apparatus and sperm ultrastructure. Zoomorphology, 131, 115 - 125. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00435 - 012 - 0147 - 2" type="journal article" year="2012">
Todaro 
<emphasis box="[1306,1357,1436,1461]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="500">et al</emphasis>
. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
, 2014, 2015) could confirm or disprove the current in-group systematization of the family 
<taxonomicName authority="(Guidi et al. 2014)" authorityName="Guidi" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Guidi" baseAuthorityYear="2014" class="Gastrotricha (awaiting allocation)" family="Planodasyidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macrodasyida" pageId="5" pageNumber="500" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="family">
Planodasyidae (
<bibRefCitation author="Guidi, L. &amp; Todaro, M. A. &amp; Ferraguti, M. &amp; Balsamo, M." pageId="5" pageNumber="500" pagination="119 - 131" refId="ref8594" refString="Guidi, L., Todaro, M. A., Ferraguti, M. &amp; Balsamo, M. (2014) Reproductive system and spermatozoa ultrastructure support the phylogenetic proximity of Megadasys and Crasiella (Gastrotricha, Macrodasyida). Contributions to Zoology, 83, 119 - 131." type="journal article" year="2014">
Guidi 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="500">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. In our opinion, and as a possible working hypothesis, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rao in Rao &amp; Clausen" authorityYear="1970" box="[864,993,1508,1533]" class="Gastrotricha (awaiting allocation)" family="Planodasyidae" genus="Planodasys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macrodasyida" pageId="5" pageNumber="500" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[864,993,1508,1533]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="500">Planodasys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Clausen" authorityYear="1968" box="[182,287,1543,1568]" class="Gastrotricha (awaiting allocation)" family="Planodasyidae" genus="Crasiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macrodasyida" pageId="5" pageNumber="500" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[182,287,1543,1568]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="500">Crasiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as it lacks reliable autapomorphic traits that could make it a distinct taxon. However, until additional information will be gathered, we continue to consider 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rao in Rao &amp; Clausen" authorityYear="1970" box="[758,887,1580,1605]" class="Gastrotricha (awaiting allocation)" family="Planodasyidae" genus="Planodasys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macrodasyida" pageId="5" pageNumber="500" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[758,887,1580,1605]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="500">Planodasys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a separate genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
